early throttled down from the default 32 MiB and needs reverting. For the rollback script, I'll use `RESET CLUSTER SETTING` for the cluster settings and either `ALTER RANGE default CONFIGURE ZONE DISCARD` to remove the custom zone config entirely or set the GC TTL back to 90000 seconds. The RANGE default zone is the only one that's been customized—it has gc.ttlseconds set to 14400 instead of the default 90000. All the other zones (system database, lease table, liveness range, and various stats tables) are using their expected system defaults, so I don't need to modify those.\n\nFor the StatefulSet, the spec shows 3 replicas and the status confirms all 3 are ready and running, which matches the original configuration. The \"replica counts\" mentioned in the problem might be referring to the zone config num_replicas settings rather than the StatefulSet itself, and those all look standard too. Writing the rollback script... Writing the rollback script... Finishing the script to verify the remaining non-default settings and confirm everything's been reverted properly. I'm also double-checking the default values I used—the snapshot rebalance rate, diagnostics reporting, and garbage collection TTL all align with CockroachDB 24.1 documentation, so using RESET commands handles them correctly.\n\nNow I'll write this script to a temporary file and create the ConfigMap from it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3917,"cache_read_input_tokens":29972,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3917},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c2c1e21-a247-40e9-a634-bebedab6ee90","uuid":"9b35a8d1-e779-4d9d-96ab-75d9dc5bb42b","request_id":"req_011Cc2eV7DMtgU5xEuPBNuTi"}
